                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>(۱) فقرنامه (۲) فیض نامه (۳) تراش نامه</p>
                            <p>This MS. was one of the four bought of J. J. Naaman on May 22, 1901,
                                and is described under the heading "(23) C. 9 (Turkish)" on
                                pp. 30-31 (562-563) of Further Notes. It contains, besides an
                                untitled tract (ff. 1b-17a), the Faqr-náma of Vírání Dedé (ff.
                                17a-51b), the Fayd-náma (ff. 51b-76a), and the Tirásh-náma (ff.
                                76a-77a).</p>
                            <p>Ff. 79 of 22.8 x 13.3 c. and 21 ll.; large, clear Turkish naskh with
                                rubrications; dated 1059/1649.</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="E_14-item1">
